  <main class="container-fluid" id="faq">
    <div class="row">
      <div class="column col-md-12">
        <h1>Frequently Asked Questions</h1>
        <hr>
      </div>

      <div class="column col-md-12">
        <div class="question">
          <p>
            What is Nexus?
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="answer">
          <p>
            Nexus is the Annual 3 Day Inter-College Cultural Festival of Sri Venkateswara College,
            New Delhi which is being organised jointly by the Fine Arts Association and Student's
            Union from last 40 years. <br>
            This year in February'19, Nexus is presenting its 41st edition.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="column col-md-12">
        <div class="question">
          <p>
            When is Nexus'19 scheduled to be held?
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="answer">
          <p>
            The three day cultural extravaganza will take place on <em> 21,22 and 23 February 2019</em> in the campus of Sri Venkateswara College, New Delhi.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="column col-md-12">
        <div class="question">
          <p>
            What is the theme of Nexus'19?
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="answer">
          <p>
            The theme for Nexus'19 is <em>Carnival D' Incredible</em>.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="column col-md-12">
        <div class="question">
          <p>
            How to reach at Sri Venkateswara College, New Delhi ?
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="answer">
          <p>
            From Indira Gandhi International Airport: <br />
            SVC is situated about 11.7 kms away from IGI Airport. A pre-paid taxi or a radiotaxi can also be taken from the airport.
            <br />


            The most convenient transport is Delhi Metro. <br />
            <em>Durgabai Deshmukh South Campus</em> (Pink Line) metro station is the nearest metro station to the college campus.
            More information for Delhi Metro is available at <a href="http://www.delhimetrorail.com/" target="_blank">http://www.delhimetrorail.com/</a>. <br />
            And Regarding Metro Route refer: <a href="http://www.delhimetrorail.com/zoom-map.jpg">http://www.delhimetrorail.com/zoom-map.jpg</a>



            <h2> GET DIRECTIONS </h2>

            Sri Venkateswara College <br />
            Dhaula Kuan Enclave I, Dhaula Kuan, New Delhi, Delhi 110021. <br />
            <br>
            011 2411 2196
            <a href="https://maps.app.goo.gl/PXsyU">Google Maps</a>



          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="column col-md-12">
        <div class="question">
          <p>
            Are personal vehicles allowed inside the college campus?
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="answer">
          <p>
            No, personal vehicles are not allowed inside the college campus.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="column col-md-12">
        <div class="question">
          <p>
            How is a participant's performance recognised at the festival?
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="answer">
          <p>
            For formal events, winning participants are rewarded with certificates and cash prizes which can go as high as ₹ 6000 (depending upon the event).
            For the informal events, winning participants, i.e. the first and second position holders are rewarded with cash prizes of ₹ 1000 and ₹ 500 respectively.

          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="column col-md-12">
        <div class="question">
          <p>
            From where can a participant get the latest updates related to Nexus'19?
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="answer">
          <p>
            Please follow Fine Arts Association and Nexus on Snapchat, Instagram and Facebook:- <br>
            Fine Arts Association:
